Former Liverpool striker and manager, Kenny Dalglish has been sent home from hospital after being diagnosed with Coronavirus, and will now continue his recovery in self-isolation, BBC reports. DAILY POST reported that Liverpool legend, Kenny Dalglish, was admitted in hospital after he tested positive for the deadly Coronavirus disease He was routinely checked for Coronavirus and tested positive despite showing no symptoms. Dalglish who was released on Sunday thanked NHS staff for their hard work after being discharged. He said, “People may think my name got me the best of care but every patient in the NHS gets the best of care. “As a nation, we are lucky to have them and I wish them all well as they work tirelessly to help the country through this pandemic.”